main event: Two luminous, seemingly elliptical objects were observed over Kelly AFB, Texas on 12 January 1953.
interesting points: The objects were traveling at a constant speed and altitude in a southwesterly direction until they disappeared.
The objects were estimated to be traveling about twice as fast as a fast jet aircraft.
The objects appeared to be about as large as a dime held at arm's length.
The observers were two experienced Air Police investigators who realized the importance of accurate observation.
No photographs or other physical evidence of the sighting was obtained.
witnesses: two Kelly AFB Air Police officers
